@George Strahm Well, you seem very sure of yourself, of course, but I still disagree from what I've seen from the hundreds of lectures and videos I've seen on the subject. Joel Salatin says he gets 4 times as many cow days per acre as his neighbors do, and he uses no expensive inputs. He follows the cows with chickens a few days after the cows are moved, which spread the manure, and he makes money on the chickens both through eggs and meat.

